                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Hyderabad, Aug. 19: A local court will hear arguments on the charges against former Satyam chairman B. Ramalinga Raju and nine other accused in the accounting scam on August 24. The CBI has informed the XXI additional chief metropolitan magistrate about its allegations against the accused in two main chargesheets and a supplementary chargesheet.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 19: Vedanta Group, pursuing a $9.6-billion takeover of Cairn India, will get an estimated windfall of Rs 500 crore if the target firms Scottish promoters fail to get shareholders nod for the deal or solicit a rival bid.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 19: The government today said it was not possible to implement the Supreme Court order that asked the Centre to distribute foodgrain for free to the poor instead of allowing it to rot because of lack of storage facility.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 19: Mercedes Benz has strengthened its E-Class models with a cabriolet version that was launched in New Delhi on Tuesday.
                                                                                                                          
